WorldStage NewsOnline— The Nigeria Police Force (NPF) has issued a final warning to those who may want to undermine the electoral process, by snatching ballot boxes to steer clear of polling stations during the Saturday elections. In a statement issued by the Force Spokesman, ACP Frank Mba in Abuja, the acting Inspector-General of Police (I-G), Mr Mohammed Adamu, said those who would be engaged in ballot box snatching, hate speeches and vote trading would face the full consequences of the law. He said adequate security measures have been put in place to ensure safe, secure and conducive environment for a peaceful and credible election. “The I-G therefore call on the citizens to come out en-masse on Saturday to cast their votes without any fear or apprehension,“he said. He reassured that security personnel deployed for the elections  have been trained and under strict instruction to abide by the Standard Operational Procedures of the force. “They will remain patriotic, steadfast, professional, neutral and civil, but firm in their conducts and actions throughout the period and beyond,“he said.